Step 1: Calculate the Current Ratio.
• The Current Assets (End_amount from the balance sheet) = 9,891,156.92.
• The Current Liabilities (End_amount from the balance sheet) = 631,880.98.
• Current Ratio = Current Assets / Current Liabilities = 9,891,156.92 / 631,880.98 ≈ 15.66.

Step 2: Calculate the Inventory Turnover Ratio.
• From the income statement, Cost of Goods Sold (COGS) = 1,337,000.00.
• The inventory at the beginning (initial amount) is 0 and at the end is 343,000.00, so the average inventory = (0 + 343,000.00) / 2 = 171,500.00.
• Inventory Turnover Ratio = COGS / Average Inventory = 1,337,000.00 / 171,500.00 = 7.80.

Thus, the solution in the required format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Current Ratio": "15.66",
    "Inventory Turnover Ratio": "7.80"
  }
}
